SIMPLE: bitch
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bitch
<hw>Bitch</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧ch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>biche</ets>, <ets>bicche</ets>, AS. <ets>bicce</ets>; cf. Icel.
<ets>bikkja</ets>, G. <ets>betze</ets>, <ets>peize</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The female of the canine kind, as of the dog, wolf, and
fox.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An opprobrious name for a woman, especially a lewd
woman.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>an unpleasant, malicious, or offensive
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>something difficult or unpleasant.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>a <er>complaint</er>.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bitch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bitch
<hw>Bitch</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧ch)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>to complain in
a whining or grumbling manner; to gripe.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bitching</ent>⟦br⟧
